      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Yield force QoI comparison — FEA vs. experiment",
      "description": "The FEA ensemble predicted yield force (defined as 0.2% offset from the linear elastic regime on the force-displacement curve) was evaluated against experimental yield force measurements from both laboratories. Across all 11 specimens the experimental mean yield force was 1 423 N (SD 98 N). The FEA ensemble mean was 1 388 N, a difference of 2.5%. E/uval = 1.12, satisfying the <1.96 acceptance criterion. The comparison was executed as part of the formal QoI validation protocol documented in the model validation report (DePuy Synthes internal report DS-VV-2023-041, Rev B). The analysis used calibrated material properties derived from coupon tensile testing of the same titanium alloy lot, and boundary conditions replicated the ASTM F1717 fixture geometry to within 0.1 mm. Inter-laboratory variability was accounted for by pooling residuals and computing a combined experimental uncertainty estimate per ASME V&V 40 Appendix C. Both laboratories reported calibration traceability to NIST standards. The result is considered fully representative of the COU loading scenario.",
