    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-requirement factor (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) is acknowledged; however, ASTM F1717 specifies a single standard test configuration for regulatory submissions, and the deviation is consistent with standard industry practice for this device class. All three pre-specified QoIs satisfy the quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96; percentage difference < 10%). The FEA modeling framework is accepted as sufficiently credible for the stated COU.",
